## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design cross-account access with least privilege, IAM trust policies, KMS, and auditing; understands CloudTrail, bucket policies.

## Key Concepts
- Cross-account IAM roles and trust policies
- S3 bucket policies and access controls
- KMS key policies and encryption scope
- CloudTrail validation and rotation awareness

## Code Example
```json
{
  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",
  \"Statement\": [
    {
      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",
      \"Principal\": {\"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_A:role/ServiceRoleA\"},
      \"Action\": \"sts:AssumeRole\"
    }
  ]
}
```

```json
{
  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",
  \"Statement\": [
    {
      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",
      \"Principal\": {\"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_A:role/ServiceRoleA\"},
      \"Action\": \"s3:GetObject\",
      \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:s3:::bucket-b/data/*\"
    },
    {
      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",
      \"Principal\": {\"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_A:role/ServiceRoleA\"},
      \"Action\": \"s3:ListBucket\",
      \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:s3:::bucket-b\"
    }
  ]
}
```

```json
{
  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",
  \"Statement\": [
    {
      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",
      \"Principal\": {\"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_B:role/DataReadRole\"},
      \"Action\": [\"kms:Decrypt\",\"kms:Encrypt\",\"kms:ReEncrypt*\",\"kms:GenerateDataKey*\"],
      \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:kms:REGION:ACCOUNT_B:key/KEYID\"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle key rotation frequency and auditing across accounts?
- How would you test access isolation and ensure no other principals can assume the role?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests cross-account trust, least privilege S3/KMS usage, no Internet constraint, and auditability.

## Key Concepts
- Cross-account role trust
- S3 bucket policy with path-level scoping
- KMS policy for decrypt/encrypt
- No Internet access
- Immutable auditing

