## Why This Is Asked
Tests understanding of least privilege, data security in transit/at rest, cross-account auditing, and implementing simple defense-in-depth for a common ingestion pattern.

## Key Concepts
- Presigned URLs, Lambda IAM, S3 bucket policies
- SSE-KMS and CMK rotation
- S3 Object Lock and immutable logs
- CloudTrail integration
- Input validation (Content-Type, size)

## Code Example
```javascript
// Minimal Lambda presigned URL generator outline
const AWS = require('aws-sdk');
const s3 = new AWS.S3();
exports.handler = async (event) => {
  const {filename, contentType, size}=JSON.parse(event.body);
  if (!contentType.startsWith('image/') || size>5*1024*1024) throw new Error('Invalid');
  const url = s3.getSignedUrl('putObject', {Bucket:'image-upload-bucket',Key:filename,ContentType:contentType,Expires:300});
  return {statusCode:200, body: JSON.stringify({url})};
};
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you rotate the CMK and rotate keys used in the bucket policy without breaking existing uploads?
- What logging verifications would you run to confirm immutability and no unauthorized uses?

## Why This Is Asked
