## Why This Is Asked
Tests a practical tenant isolation pattern in a single AWS account using core services, focusing on real-world constraints for beginners.

## Key Concepts
- Tenant isolation with DynamoDB LeadingKeys and per-tenant partition keys
- IAM policy conditions using ForAllValues:StringEquals and PrincipalTag
- API Gateway/Lambda authorizer to inject TenantId into requests
- Auditing and testability with CloudTrail data events

## Code Example
```javascript
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["dynamodb:GetItem","dynamodb:PutItem","dynamodb:Query"],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:dynamodb:region:acct:table/TenantTable",
      "Condition": {
        "ForAllValues:StringEquals": {
          "dynamodb:LeadingKeys": ["TENANT#${aws:PrincipalTag/TenantId}"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

