## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical knowledge of securing a basic AWS web app stack with enforceable, testable controls. It emphasizes automation (infrastructure as code), data protection, and monitoring.

## Key Concepts
- Infrastructure as Code (CDK/CFN)
- S3 public access blocks and SSE-KMS
- DynamoDB encryption at rest with CMK rotation
- VPC Endpoints for private service access
- Immutable logging with CloudTrail, Config, GuardDuty
- Access analysis and drift testing

## Code Example
```javascript
// Minimal CDK outline (-typescript) showing S3, DynamoDB, and endpoints
import * as cdk from 'aws-cdk-lib';
import { Bucket, BlockPublicAccess } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-s3';
import { Table, AttributeType } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-dynamodb';
import { Vpc, InterfaceEndpointType } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-ec2';

class SecBaselineStack extends cdk.Stack {
  constructor(scope: cdk.App, id: string) {
    super(scope, id);
    const vpc = new Vpc(this, 'VPC');
    const bucket = new Bucket(this, 'DataBucket', {
      blockPublicAccess: BlockPublicAccess.BLOCK_ALL,
      encryption: s3.BucketEncryption.KMS,
      encryptionKey: kmsKey,
    });
    const tbl = new Table(this, 'DataTable', {
      partitionKey: { name: 'id', type: AttributeType.STRING },
      encryption: TableEncryption.KMS,
      encryptionKey: kmsKey,
    });
    // Endpoints and policy snippets omitted for brevity
  }
}
```

